
 * if we set our bean to be lazy loaded then will be loaded when it's needed (when we call methods from him, when we try to use it)

WORTH TO NOTE:

 * if our bean is not set to be lazy loaded then will be loaded before ApplicationContext is fully initialized,
 so init method of a bean will be called before we have an access to ApplicationContext

 * by default all beans are initialized at the application startup,
